onses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPresence of pus in the joint\u003C/strong\u003E is a hallmark of septic arthritis. The infection leads to the accumulation of purulent material within the joint space, which can cause significant damage to the hyaline cartilage if not treated promptly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbsence of joint swelling\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as septic arthritis typically presents with a swollen joint due to inflammation and effusion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal inflammatory markers\u003C/strong\u003E are unlikely in septic arthritis, as the condition usually causes elevated markers such as C-reactive protein and erythrocyte sedimentation rate due to the systemic inflammatory response.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommon occurrence in adults\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While septic arthritis can occur in adults, it is more common in children, particularly those under the age of 15.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPresence of joint effusion without pain\u003C/strong\u003E is not typical of septic arthritis, which usually presents with significant pain and tenderness in the affected joint.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute haematogenous septic arthritis is more common in children than adults.","Septic arthritis typically presents with a swollen, painful joint.","Pus in the joint can lead to destruction of hyaline cartilage if not treated promptly."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Osteomyelitis. [Updated 2023 May 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532250/","Folpe, A., \u0026 Nielsen, G. P. (Eds.). (2022). Bone and Soft 